title: Human Resources - Behavior and Diversity in the Workplace
headline: Learn Human Resources, Behavior, and Diversity in the Workplace with this free online course.
description: This free online course Human Resources - Behavior and Diversity in the Workplace, teaches students about many of the key aspects to human resources today. courseDescription:
This course, Human Resources - Behavior and Diversity in the Workplace, will provide you with an understanding of the human resource management. You will be able to explain recruiting and interviewing along with retention and orientation. You will also learn about following up with new employees as well as workplace health and safety. Students will also learn about workplace bullying, harassment, and violence as well as workplace wellness. You will also learn about providing feedback to employees.

 

This course then explains Developing Corporate Behavior. You will learn about the science of behavior as well as the benefits for corporate behavior. You will also learn about the most common categories of corporate behavior. Students will also learn about managerial structure, and employee accountability.

 

This course then wraps up with a lesson on workplace diversity. You will learn about understanding diversity and stereotypes and how to use this understanding to break down barriers. This part out the course teaches verbal and non-verbal communication skills. By taking this course you will learn how to properly run all of the human resources aspects of your business. So why wait? Start learning today.
